<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8212542>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–2. 1, Colonyof Tadarida brasiliensis at the building of the Law Faculty (National University of Rosario,Argentina). 2, Cluster with juveniles in the bat colony of Tadarida brasiliensis (National University of Rosario, Argentina)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8212542/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8212544>
    dc:description "FIGURES 3–6. 3, Propicimex tucmatiani (Wygodzinsky, 1951), a male found at INTA Delta Station, dorsal view. 4, Same individual, terminalia. 5, Terminalia of a conspecific female from the same collecting event. 6, Rock formation at El Trébol Lagoon, west of San Carlos de Bariloche, Río Negro (41.065°S, 71.495°W) examined looking for the presence of Bertilia valdiviana in December 2018." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8212544/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

